<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-44-1052 </DOCNO><TEXT>Outlines efforts in rescue, supply, communications and medical aid ofminers trapped underground via small diameter (80 mm) boreholes. A 70mm diameter information sonde, developed in the GDR, is passed throughthe borehole. It contains light source, oral communication system andcardiorespiratory monitor. Further 70 mm diameter transport containersfor food and other needed articles are available. Monitoring of cardiorespiratorysignals at the central display is described. Communication with trappedminers, remote diagnosis of their state of health, possible therapy andrecommended diets are also reviewed. Further internationally availablerescue equipment for supply through boreholes is noted. 9 refs.</TEXT></DOC>